    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen treesitter experience slow performance, this carry over to basic vim operations such as simple editing or logging (e.g. `G`), see for example https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/24965\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWould it be possible to do the treesitter work in a separate thread or in some other manor to interfere  less with just moving around?\r\n\r\nFor example, does scrolling with capital G need to perform treesitter queries at all?",
    "closed_at": "2024-03-24T21:21:26Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Performance improvements are already tracked elsewhere. Since the highlighter runs in a fast loop, we cannot just offload this easily to a separate thread. \n\nAnd, yes, scrolling needs to trigger the parser since we only run injections for the visible region -- for performance reasons. ",
